Instruction: With the load module still isolated, disconnect one lead of each lamp from the rest of the internal wiring so that each lamp is fully isolated. Then, using a current‑limited bench supply, drive each lamp directly: start at 1–2 V and ramp up toward 12 V while monitoring current and observing for illumination. Compare actual I–V behavior and turn‑on to expected (≈100 mA at 12 V for 120 Ω, ≈24 mA for 500 Ω). Record whether either lamp lights, draws current, or remains dark/open under direct drive.
